modules.description: Handles event sequencing and port management with methods to create, close, and trigger output events on specific ports. Operates on a custom type `t` and processes input data as arrays of integer tuples. Used to coordinate hardware signals in real-time systems by routing and timing data through defined ports.

Provides functions to parse and validate JSON strings, extract values by key, and handle nested object structures. Operates on strings, JSON values, and associative arrays represented as lists of key-value pairs. Used to process configuration data from external sources and transform it into structured OCaml records.

manages event sequencing and port operations, allowing creation, closure, and triggering of output events on specific ports. It works with a custom type `t` and processes input as arrays of integer tuples, enabling precise control over hardware signal routing and timing. Users can define event flows, manage port states, and synchronize data transmission in real-time applications. Examples include coordinating sensor data output or managing communication between embedded system components.
